The paper deals with downlink channel estimation in massive MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of high-resolution channel estimation, which falls under signal processing (cs.SI). The use of multiple antennas is a key aspect of the paper, making it relevant to the sub-category of massive MIMO (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of channel extrapolation, which is a topic related to communication engineering (cs.CE).
